OL,3,CGym, cinema and sauna: Life on 'hotel'
OL,4,Cgas platform 18 miles offshore
OL,6,FDuring their down time, as well as the
OL,7,Fcinema and gym, workers have access to
OL,8,Fa pool room and dartboard - and even a
OL,9,Fyoga space.
OL,11,FThe work itself is demanding - staff
OL,12,Fmanage the flow of billions of cubic
OL,13,Ffeet of methane in and out of the
OL,14,Fnational network. Maintaining a
OL,15,Fstructure that's spent 40 years semi
OL,16,Fsubmerged in salt water is a big task
OL,17,F- and not short of risk.
OL,19,FThat's why help is on hand - even in
OL,20,Fthe most remote of workplaces.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G10/12
